logistic Regression¶

In [16]:
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
lr = LogisticRegression()
lr.fit(x_train,y_train)
predictions = lr.predict(x_test)
print(confusion_matrix(y_test, predictions))
print(classification_report(y_test, predictions))
print(accuracy_score(y_test, predictions))

Q1)Your views about the problem statement? ans: In this problem statement I have to predicted the rainfall using various model like logistic Regression,Decision Tree,Random Forest Classifier.

Q2) What will be your approach to solving this task? Ans: Step-1 Importing all the neccessary library like pandas,numpy and seaborn step 2 cleaning the data like dropping null and missing values step3 visualising the data using scatter plot step4. finding accuracy score,classificatio report and confusion matrix using various models like logistic. regression,decision tree and. Random forest classifier

Q3)What were the available ML model options you had to perform this task? Ans: Logistic Regression,Decision Matrix and Random Matrix Classifier

Q4). Which model’s performance is best and what could be the possible reason for that? Ans: Logistic regression model's perfomance is best because it is predicting better than other models.

Q5) What steps can you take to improve this selected model’s performance even further? Ans: i)By choosing a robust algorithm: Choosing the right algorithm is dependent on: -The specific requirements of your model. -The type of data you are working with. -The problem you are trying to solve.

ii)Improve Model : This step is crucial in achieving an improved model and its quality.

iii)Ensemble Learning :By mixing the predictions from various models, ensemble learning is a broad meta-approach to machine learning that aims to improve model performance.
